    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>General term referring to all birds of prey of either Falconiformes or Strigiformes orders, including hawks, eagles, vultures, falcons, and owls, having in common a hooked beak, sharp talons, and keen eyesight.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
